<p>Is there any standard for tolerable delay in audio and video communication for web ? I have noticed delay using my WebRTC application and want to compare it with the standard (if any).</p>  <p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latency_%28audio%29" rel="nofollow">Wikipedia</a> has mentioned following delays:</p>  <ul> <li>Live audio : several hundred ms to a few seconds,</li> <li>Telephone Calls : 200ms,</li> <li>IP calls: min 20ms, max 150ms</li> <li>Computer audio: 500ms</li> </ul>  <p>From book <a href="https://books.google.com.bd/books?id=bMKFYMql8uoC&amp;pg=PA109&amp;lpg=PA109" rel="nofollow">"Deploying QoS for Cisco IP and Next Generation Networks: The Definitive Guide" By Vinod Joseph, Brett Chapman</a>:</p>  <ul> <li>Voice : 150ms one way</li> <li>Interactive video: 150ms (upto 200ms)</li> <li>live : 150ms</li> <li>video on demand : 150ms</li> <li>Multimedia conferencing and streaming: >400ms</li> </ul>  <p>Which one should i compare with ? Interactive video, Multimedia conferencing or IP calls ?</p>